.TH "disk_flush_events" 9 "disk_flush_events" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
disk_flush_events \- schedule immediate event checking and flushing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" disk_flush_events
.BI "(struct gendisk *disk "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "disk" 12
disk to check and flush events for
.IP "mask" 12
events to flush
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Schedule immediate event checking on \fIdisk\fP if not blocked.  Events in
\fImask\fP are scheduled to be cleared from the driver.  Note that this
doesn't clear the events from \fIdisk->ev\fP.
.SH "CONTEXT"
If \fImask\fP is non-zero must be called with bdev->bd_mutex held.
